<TITLE> HSC Bengali more 'creative' from 2012 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnew24.com)  Bengali first paper of the higher secondary exams will be held in a more 'creative format' from 2012. Higher Secondary Certificate and equivalent examinations of Bengali first paper, which is typically on literature, will require more creative answers coming away from the short answers and multiple choice questions. According to a notification of the education ministry on Monday mark distribution will emphasise on the creative section allocating 60 percent marks to it. The remaining 40 percent will be allocated to multiple choice questions. Around 4500 Bengali teachers from all the colleges around the country will receive training within July to implement the new system. The 'creative format' was introduced for the first time through the Bengali first paper and Religious Studies examination in the SSC level in 2010. The notification also says that in the next SSC examination in 2011, five other subjects--general science, social science, geography, chemistry and introduction to commerce will be held in the creative format. The rest of the subjects  physics, biology, history, economics, accounting, commerce, home economics, agriculture and computer science  will follow suit in the next year's SSC exams. b
